4 consent, or lacks the capacity to consent, or by the use of
5 forcible compulsion. Forcible compulsion includes the use
6 of a substance administered without a victim's knowledge or
7 consent which renders the victim physically or mentally
8 impaired so as to be incapable of making an informed consent
